reviewText: The Cyberchase DVDs introduce math concepts in a fun and creative manner through the use of great characters.  Each episode also includes a "For Real" section that applies the math concept to an everyday situation.  Highly recommend any of the Cyberchase shows!

My son has been watching this show for a year or so, but has recently become an official addict.  Whenever he has the choice of selecting a program, we know it's going to be Cyberchase (EVERY time).  He's still too young to really understand the concepts completely, but it's a good, practical introduction to math and the characters are engaging (although there's no real way to make Gilbert Gottfried's voice pleasurable to the human ear).  We also love the "Cyberchase For Real!" segments at the end of each episode - Harry and Bianca rock.  Look for random cameos throughout the seasons from Tony Hawk, Matthew Broderick, Al Roker, Bebe Neuwirth, and Adam Levine.
Cyberchase is one of the best shows for kids. Fun,educational and exciting. My son loves this show and will continue to watch it!!!

they teach kids math and science under the guise of scifi cyber adventures. If seen them teach basic concepts of statistics, Cartesian coordinates, fractions, algebra, and the basic laws of motion. great voice acting from Christopher Lloyd and Gilbert Godfried too.

Cyberchase is an American/Canadian television series for children ages 7-13. The series takes place in Cyberspace, a virtual world, and chronicles the adventures of three children, Jackie, Inez, and Matt, as they use math and problem solving skills to save Cyberspace and its leader, Motherboard, from The Hacker, the villain.

This is an incredible series that introduces fairly sophisticated mathematical concepts in easy to understand (and entertaining) ways.  My girls 4 and 6 love Cyberchase and I dearly wish there were more episodes!
Cyber chase is a favorite in our home. My kids love it and I am amazed at the incredible creativity with which the show teaches foundational math concepts. This show is a must see!!!!

Hi Amazon. I wanted to let you know that I haven't watched Cyberchase Season 1 (or any of the subsequent seasons, if they exist). While I'm sure I'd love it, I'm a 43 year old father of two with a job and the harsh reality is that my busy lifestyle has made me cut way back on cartoons. (Though I'm typically more into the ones where anvils fall on Coyote.) My kids seem to have spent some time on Amazon Prime checking out Cyberchase. I think you should think about truing up those algorithms to figure out which review solicitations do and do not apply to me.
